@node Introduction, Getting started, Top, Top
@chapter Introduction

Porky is a Common Lisp library for working with the Semantic Web.  It
is an amalgam of Ora Lassila's Wilbur library, several Wilbur
extensions from Richard Newman, and some new code from others.

@node Getting started, Basic usage, Introduction, Top
@chapter Getting started

You can get the Porky source code using the Git version control
system@footnote{Git is available from @url{http://git.or.cz}.}.  The
repository is hosted at
@url{http://github.com/davelambert/porky/tree/master}.

@smallexample
$ git clone git://github.com/davelambert/porky.git
@end smallexample

This should leave you with a new directory called @file{porky}.  See
the file @file{porky/INSTALL} for installation instructions.

@node Basic usage, Function Index, Getting started, Top
@chapter Basic usage

@smallexample
> (wilbur:db-load (make-instance 'wilbur:db) *xmlrdf-file*)

> (wilbur:db-load (make-instance 'wilbur:db) *xmlrdf-file*
                  :parser-class 'wilbur:rdf-parser)

> (wilbur:db-load (make-instance 'porky.io.turtle:turtle-db) *turtle-file*
                  :parser-class 'porky.io.turtle::turtle-parser)
@end smallexample

